    "system_description": "Korean case particle + verb ending disambiguation. Like Japanese, postpositional particles mark argument roles (이/가 i/ga subject, 을/를 eul/reul object, 에/에서 e/eseo location, 한테/에게 hante/ege recipient). Topic marker 은/는 eun/neun parallels Japanese は wa. Korean verb endings are highly agglutinative and encode tense, aspect, mood, speech level, and evidentiality simultaneously. The honorific system adds a constraint channel: verb endings disambiguate the social relationship between speaker and referent.",
